  "number": 1096,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1096",
  "title": "Toggle widget displaying 0 for count when there are results",
  "body": "We are using toggle widget to check a numeric boolean value (can either be 1 or 0). It is setup like so:\n\n``` js\nthis.instantsearch.addWidget(\n    instantsearch.widgets.toggle({\n        container: '#journeys-specials-widget',\n        attributeName: 'hasSpecialOffer',\n        label: 'Only show specials',\n        values: {\n            on: 1,\n        },\n        templates: {\n            item: refinementItem\n        },\n    })\n);\n```\n\nThe filter is working as intended but is displaying an incorrect value of 0 next to the toggle as there are 40 results displayed when toggled.\n\nI feel like this has something to do with the off value not working correctly. If I set it to `0` the refinement is activated by default which isn't what we want.\n\nThe toggle was working previously when the values were `true` or `false` but our data changed and it stopped working.\n",
